cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper proposes a new method for arbitrary style transfer using a normalization module and dynamic convolution. The paper focuses on computer vision (CV) tasks and specifically on image style transfer, which suggests that cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning (ML) techniques, which makes cs.AI and cs.LG likely sub-categories. The paper introduces a lightweight architecture for style transfer, which could be relevant to graphics (GR) and multimedia (MM) sub-categories.
